description:
Welcome to the world of Shonen Jump! SJ manga is among the most popular in the world with hit series like Naruto, One Piece and Bleach.

If you want to get ahead of these stories from where the graphic novels are, try Weekly Shonen Jump! It's a digital magazine that delivers the newest chapters of these manga to the American fans on the same day as Japan! You can read it on your iOS, Android or anything with a Flash-enabled Internet browser.

A big issue to kick off the shortest month of the year! We've got all your favorites, plus some great monthlies and an amazing newcomer! We'll start with the new -- we're running parts of the Dragon Ball Z manga in color! No, we didn't color it ourselves, this came straight from Japan! Don't miss this historic occasion! As for the monthlies, we've got the newest chapters of Rurouni Kenshin: Restoration and Blue Exorcist! And another hilarious chapter of our new superhero action comedy, One-Punch Man! All this and more!

Friends

As promised at the beginning of the year, we're adding yet another manga to the already gigantic line-up! Weclome World Trigger! Giant monsters called "Neighbors" have invaded the planet, and regular weaponry is useless! Just when all seems lost, a strange group shows up and repels the monsters. Just who are these people, and how did they know about the Neighbors' technology? Plus, the second chapter of the color Dragon Ball manga! All that and a whole more in the latest issue of Weekly Shonen Jump!

Quick! Call the manga Orkin Man! The infestation in this week's issue is causing mass panic. In Yu-Gi-Oh! Zexal, Kyuji's caught in Hishakaku's tangled web, and the only way out is through... a Duel! In One-Punch Man, Saitama's bored with fighting opponents who aren't quite up to snuff, but the appearance of a mosquito-controlling babe might just be the fight he's been looking for... Yuma and Osamu's excellent adventures in World Trigger continue, but will their thrilling ride turn sour when a swarm of Neighbors attack?! Do yourself a favor and bug out with an intoxicating dose of Shonen Jump manga!
